# Design Document

Controller-first desktop game launcher for macOS (Apple Silicon first). Orbit is a modern
alternative to Pegasus Frontend, inspired by PS5, Nintendo Switch, and Apple TV.

Built with **Tauri 2**, **React**, **TypeScript**, and **SQLite**. All filesystem and
process logic lives in Rust; the frontend never launches games directly.

## Purpose

- Fullscreen, couch-friendly game library with cinematic screen transitions.
- Import games from Steam, Astris (`.nsp`/`.xci`), GameHub, macOS apps, and manual paths.
- Track playtime, install size, and achievements locally.
- Customize the entire app layout with built-in themes (PS5, Switch 2, Orbit) or user JSON themes.

## Functional requirements

- User can browse a **home** screen with hero artwork and recent-game rows.
- User can browse, filter, and sort the **library** grid.
- User can open **game details** with playtime, size, achievements, and launch action.
- User can **add games** via importer scans or manual file pick (Add game journey).
- User can **edit properties** â€” title, description, portrait/landscape/square artwork (Base64 in SQLite).
- User can **launch** a game; Orbit tracks the session and playtime.
- User can **stop** an active game session from the UI.
- User can sync **Steam** library metadata (playtime, SizeOnDisk, achievements) locally.
- User can switch **themes** including custom JSON themes from Application Support.
- User can navigate entirely with a **gamepad** or keyboard fallback.

## Non-functional requirements

- **Local-first:** SQLite is the source of truth; no cloud sync in v1.
- **Controller-first:** spatial focus system; all primary flows reachable without a mouse.
- **macOS-first:** Apple Silicon target; fullscreen window management via Tauri.
- **Safe launch:** Rust validates paths and only launches resolved executables from known importers.
- **Performance:** avoid unbounded library loads; batch Tauri invokes where possible.

## Out of scope

ROM downloads/decryption, keys management, emulator distribution, automatic online artwork
scraping (manual search + optional RAWG key only), Steam account auth, cloud sync, social features.

