## Screens (frontend routing)

Orbit uses a Zustand-driven screen stack (`AppScreen` in `src/stores/ui.store.ts`), not URL routes.

| Screen | `AppScreen` | Purpose |
| ------ | ----------- | ------- |
| Home | `home` | Hero + recent rows; theme-specific layout (Orbit / PS5 / Switch) |
| Library | `library` | Filterable/sortable game grid |
| Search | `search` | Text search across library |
| Game details | `game-details` | Metadata, achievements, play/launch |
| Edit properties | `game-edit` | Title, description, artwork slots |
| Add game | `add-game` | Importer detection, scans, manual import |
| Settings | `settings` | Theme, RAWG key, library maintenance |

### Screen transitions

`App.tsx` wraps screens in Framer Motion `AnimatePresence` with blur/fade transitions.
`previousScreen` is preserved for back navigation.

