## Tauri command surface

All frontend I/O goes through `src/lib/tauri.ts` â†’ `invoke()`. In browser dev (no Tauri),
`src/lib/devMockApi.ts` provides mock data.

### Games & settings

| Command | Args | Returns | Notes |
| ------- | ---- | ------- | ----- |
| `list_games` | â€” | `Game[]` | Full library |
| `get_game` | `gameId` | `Game \| null` | Single record |
| `create_game` | `request: CreateGameRequest` | `Game` | Manual add |
| `update_game` | `gameId`, `request: UpdateGameRequest` | `Game` | Edit properties |
| `toggle_favorite` | `gameId` | `Game` | |
| `set_game_hidden` | `gameId`, `hidden` | `Game` | |
| `delete_game` | `gameId` | `void` | Blocked if game is actively running |
| `clear_library` | â€” | `number` | Count removed; blocked if session active |
| `get_setting` | `key` | `T \| null` | e.g. `themeId`, `rawgApiKey` |
| `set_setting` | `key`, `value` | `void` | JSON-serialized in SQLite |

### Sessions & window

| Command | Args | Returns | Notes |
| ------- | ---- | ------- | ----- |
| `launch_game` | `gameId` | `GameSession` | Spawns process via `launching/` |
| `stop_game` | `sessionId` | `GameSession` | User-initiated stop |
| `get_active_session` | â€” | `GameSession \| null` | |
| `set_window_fullscreen` | `fullscreen` | `void` | |
| `hide_orbit_window` | â€” | `void` | During gameplay |
| `show_orbit_window` | â€” | `void` | After session ends |

### Importers

| Command | Args | Returns | Notes |
| ------- | ---- | ------- | ----- |
| `detect_importers` | â€” | `ImporterStatus[]` | Steam, Astris, native, GameHub |
| `scan_steam_library` | â€” | `ScanResult` | Upserts via `LibrarySyncService` |
| `scan_astris_folder` | `folder` | `ScanResult` | User-selected folder |
| `scan_native_apps` | â€” | `ScanResult` | macOS `/Applications` |
| `scan_gamehub_folder` | `folder?` | `ScanResult` | Experimental |
| `import_game_path` | `path` | `ScanResult` | Manual file/folder pick |

### Themes & artwork

| Command | Args | Returns | Notes |
| ------- | ---- | ------- | ----- |
| `list_custom_themes` | â€” | `ThemeDefinition[]` | From Application Support |
| `themes_directory` | â€” | `string` | Path to custom themes folder |
